ackage is new<br />&gt; too.<br /><br />Well, the "idle_buddy" thing on its own could be considered to be<br />purely a caching thing.<br /><br />Sure, it doesn't take tsk_cpus_allowed() into account while setting up<br />the cache (since it's not dynamic enough), but *assuming* the common<br />case is that people let threads be on any of the cores of a package,<br />it should be possible to make the cache 100% equivalent with no<br />semantic change. No?<br /><br />The code doesn't even try to do that kind of "don't change semantics",<br />though, and makes the idle-buddy thing entirely different.<br /><br />            Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
